{{Infobox NRHP | name = Sharon Lutheran Church and Cemetery | designated_other1 = Virginia Landmarks Register | designated_other1_date = June 21, 1978<ref name=register>{{cite web|title=Virginia Landmarks Register|url=http://www.dhr.virginia.gov/registers/register_counties_cities.htm|publisher=Virginia Department of Historic Resources|accessdate=19 March 2013}}</ref> | designated_other1_number = 010-0040 | designated_other1_num_position = bottom | nrhp_type = | image = Sharon Lutheran Church near Ceres.jpg | caption = Overview from the west | location= West of Ceres on State Route 42, near [[Ceres, Virginia]] | coordinates = {{coord|37|0|59|N|81|20|57|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = Virginia#USA | built = 1817, 1883 | architecture = | added = February 28, 1979 | area = {{convert|4|acre}} | refnum = 79003030<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|2009a}}</ref> }}
'''Sharon Lutheran Church and Cemetery''' is a historic [[Lutheranism|Lutheran]] [[Church (building)|church]] and cemetery located near [[Ceres, Virginia|Ceres]], [[Bland County, Virginia]]. The church was built in 1883, and is a one-story, frame church, four bays long, with round-arched, stained-glass windows and a gable roof. It features a projecting square tower with a bell-cast pyramidal roof and cross finial on the entrance facade. The adjacent cemetery was established in 1817, and includes a collection of rare Germanic gravestones which are stylistically related to those found in the outlying churches of the [[Wythe County, Virginia|Wythe County]] German settlements.<ref name=VAnom>{{cite web|url=http://www.dhr.virginia.gov/registers/Counties/Bland/010-0040_Sharon_Lutheran_Church_and_Cemetery_1979_Final_Nomination.pdf|title=National Register of Historic Places Inventory/Nomination: Sharon Lutheran Church and Cemetery |author=Virginia Historic Landmarks Commission Staff|date= November 1978}} and [http://www.dhr.virginia.gov/registers/Counties/Bland/Sharon_Lutheran_photo.htm ''Accompanying photo'']</ref>
It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1979.<ref name=nris/>
